smoky fumes with a smell of burnt rubber from the engine hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Misfire and Spark Plug Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine misfires and spark plug issues can cause engine damage, reduce fuel efficiency, and lead to costly repairs.

The failure of ignition coils can cause engine performance issues, such as poor acceleration, jerky driving, and check engine light illumination, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the transmission can cause sudden deceleration, stalling, and loss of power, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

The failure of engine cylinders can cause engine performance issues, such as poor acceleration, jerky driving, and check engine light illumination, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the keyless entry module can cause issues with starting the vehicle, which can lead to inconvenience and safety risks.
